25|$|Patten {{introduced}} {{a package of}} <b>electoral</b> <b>reforms</b> in the Legislative Council. These reforms proposed to enlarge the electorate, thus making voting in the Legislative Council more democratic. This move posed significant changes because Hong Kong citizens would {{have the power to}} make decisions regarding their future.|$|E
25|$|Catholics were {{excluded}} from qualifying as voters until 1793 and taking seats in Parliament until 1829 {{and there was a}} restrictive property based franchise. It was not until the <b>electoral</b> <b>reforms</b> which took effect in 1885 that most adult males became voters. See Catholic emancipation for further details.|$|E
